public final class Location
extends com.google.api.client.json.GenericJson

Model definition for Latitude.Location. A Location resource identifies a user's position at a particular time. It may include metadata about the user's position, such as a venue if the location was recorded at the time of a check- in. This class models an object which will be transmitted to or from the Latitude service. To reduce the data transferred during service requests, you may remove members that contain data elements that your application does not need. For a detailed explanation, see: http://code.google.com/p/google-api-java-client/wiki/Json
